<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Species complex. 
<bibRefCitation author="Arias, A." journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="345 - 369" title="Onuphis and Aponuphis (Annelida: Onuphidae) from southwestern Europe, with the description of a new species" volume="3949" year="2015">Arias and Paxton (2015a)</bibRefCitation>
consider 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Onuphidae" genus="Aponuphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aponuphis fauveli" order="Eunicida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fauveli">Aponuphis fauveli</taxonomicName>
a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. brementi" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" rank="species" species="brementi">A. brementi</taxonomicName>
, thus literature records of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Onuphidae" genus="Aponuphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aponuphis fauveli" order="Eunicida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fauveli">Aponuphis fauveli</taxonomicName>
are here assigned to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Onuphidae" genus="Aponuphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aponuphis brementi" order="Eunicida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brementi">Aponuphis brementi</taxonomicName>
. However, molecular evidence of sibling species within 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Onuphidae" genus="Aponuphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aponuphis brementi" order="Eunicida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brementi">Aponuphis brementi</taxonomicName>
were found by Borisova et al. (submitted). Type locality: Mediterranean (Bay of Roquebrun, France).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
